CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 9, 1957, pg. 10 reads: "For Recreation Center - At a recent meeting at the Homewood Library, a staff was set up for a Homewood Recreation Center, sponsored by Mrs. Minnie Fuller. Shown above  are (sitting, left to right) Daisye Lipscomb, secretary; Mrs. Fuller, head recreating leader; Lucille McKeever, and, standing, LaRue Jackson, Sampson Goodson and Edith Greene, treasurer. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Homewood Recreation Center staff, seated from left: Daisye Lipscomb, Minnie Fuller, and Lucille McKeever; standing: LaRue Jackson, Sampson Goodson, and Edith Greene, gathered at table in Homewood Library
